{"title":"Cyber Cycles Cross Blade Ti Fork","link":"https://theradavist.com/cyber-cycles-cross-blade-ti-fork/","date":1712000085000,"content":"<p><img src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlades_Forks_01.jpeg?fit=1200,738&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlades_Forks_01.jpeg?w=1767&amp;quality=75 1767w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlades_Forks_01.jpeg?resize=1200,738&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlades_Forks_01.jpeg?resize=768,472&amp;quality=75 768w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlades_Forks_01.jpeg?resize=1536,945&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p>Germany’s Cyber Cycles just announced its first batch of the <a href=\"https://www.cybercycles.de/product-page/cross-blade-fork\" target=\"_blank\">Cross Blade forks with titanium legs</a> (€599)…<span></span></p>\n<p><img width=\"1200\" height=\"699\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlade_Forks_03.jpeg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlade_Forks_03.jpeg?w=1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlade_Forks_03.jpeg?resize=768,447&amp;quality=75 768w\" /></p>\n<p>Inspired by the old Bontrager forks in the 1990s, the Cross Blade fork utilizes a CNC-manufactured crown that clamps to the fork legs, allowing you to adjust the installation height from 400 mm to 430 mm and even change the fork shaft and the two blades. This means that Cyber Cycles’ entire construction kit is at your fingertips to adjust and adapt the fork as needed to fit your use case. The fork comes standard with an installation height of 430 mm, but custom lengths are available.</p>\n<p>​<img width=\"1200\" height=\"818\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlade_Forks_02.jpeg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlade_Forks_02.jpeg?w=1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/CyberCycles_CrossBlade_Forks_02.jpeg?resize=768,524&amp;quality=75 768w\" /></p>\n<p>During the design, emphasis was placed, among other things, on the long durability of the screw connections. Therefore, all threads in the crown are designed as replaceable stainless steel cross nuts. If desired, the screws can also be replaced with titanium screws.</p>\n<p><img loading=\"lazy\" width=\"1186\" height=\"1186\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_6e3d9448bc3649c5996182275.jpg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_6e3d9448bc3649c5996182275.jpg?w=1186&amp;quality=75 1186w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_6e3d9448bc3649c5996182275.jpg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_6e3d9448bc3649c5996182275.jpg?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w\" /><img loading=\"lazy\" src=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_5c823972568443af9abdef5c7-1.jpg?fit=1200,1200&amp;quality=75\" srcset=\"https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_5c823972568443af9abdef5c7-1.jpg?w=1800&amp;quality=75 1800w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_5c823972568443af9abdef5c7-1.jpg?resize=1200,1200&amp;quality=75 1200w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_5c823972568443af9abdef5c7-1.jpg?resize=150,150&amp;quality=75 150w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_5c823972568443af9abdef5c7-1.jpg?resize=768,768&amp;quality=75 768w, https://radavist-static-production.s3.amazonaws.com/uploads/2024/04/55a245_5c823972568443af9abdef5c7-1.jpg?resize=1536,1536&amp;quality=75 1536w\" /></p>\n<p><strong>​Specs:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n<li>Installation height: max. 430mm</li>\n<li>Hub standard : 12x100mm</li>\n<li>Tire clearance: 15mm at 29″x2.25″</li>\n<li>Brake base: Flat Mount Direct 160mm</li>\n<li>Shaft: Columbus Lit e – 28.6mm x 300mm</li>\n<li>Crown and dropouts: Al7075T6</li>\n<li>Blades TI : Ti3Al2.5V (1.2mm)</li>\n<li>Weight Cross Blade TI : 102 0g (shaft 190mm)</li>\n</ul>\n<p> </p>\n<p>See more at <a href=\"https://www.cybercycles.de/product-page/cross-blade-fork\" target=\"_blank\">Cyber Cycles</a>.​</p>\n<p>The post <a href=\"https://theradavist.com/cyber-cycles-cross-blade-ti-fork/\">Cyber Cycles Cross Blade Ti Fork</a> appeared first on <a href=\"https://theradavist.com\">The Radavist</a>.</p>","author":"John Watson","siteTitle":"The Radavist","siteHash":"96eb481d8084f04a4602bac57874ba717baf56b758f45547b5caf2312da766ef","entryHash":"3ab5d851c90294b779981b5f82a0b65e7878efad7e4e45473dcaa12b7fa3e51d","category":"Cycling"}